THE ELLEN BURSTYN SHOW:  ABC Weekly Situation Comedy, Produced by Ron Frazier for Walt Disney.  This series premiered September 20, 1986.
&lt;P&gt;
Burstyn plays Ellen Brewer, the head of a multi-generational household.  Brewer is an iconclastic writer-in-residence at a Baltimore college.  She holds seminars in the brownstone she shares with a hyperactive mother Sydney (Elaine Strich), 25-year-old daughter Molly (Megan Mullally) and 5-year-old grandson, Nick(Jesse R. Tendler). Theme song "Nothing in the world like love" lyrics: John Bettis, music: Artie Butler
